<div class="alert alert-info">
  <div>
    Server-side Plunk sync only needs the secret API key and API base URL. Hosted and self-hosted Plunk are both supported,
    and the connection check verifies that Spree can reach the Plunk <code>/contacts</code> API with the supplied secret key.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h3 class="h6 mb-3">Core connection settings</h3>

    <%= preference_field(
      @integration,
      form,
      "plunk_base_url",
      i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
    ) %>
    <p class="mb-4 mt-n2">
      Use the API base URL only, such as <code>https://next-api.useplunk.com</code> or
      <code>https://plunk.example.com/api</code>. Do not paste a specific endpoint like
      <code>/contacts</code>, <code>/events/track</code>, or <code>/v1/track</code>.
    </p>

    <%= preference_field(
      @integration,
      form,
      "plunk_secret_api_key",
      i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
    ) %>
    <p class="mb-0 mt-n2">
      Required for server-side contact upserts and event tracking. Paste a Plunk secret server key for this workspace;
      public or browser-side keys will fail the connection test.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h3 class="h6 mb-3">Optional sender defaults</h3>

    <%= preference_field(
      @integration,
      form,
      "default_from_email",
      i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
    ) %>
    <p class="mb-4 mt-n2">
      Optional. Use a single mailbox such as <code>marketing@example.com</code>. This does not change current MVP contact
      sync or event tracking behavior by itself.
    </p>

    <%= preference_field(
      @integration,
      form,
      "default_from_name",
      i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
    ) %>
    <p class="mb-0 mt-n2">
      Optional display name such as <code>Example Store</code>. If you set a sender name, also set a sender email so the
      stored sender identity stays complete.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h3 class="h6 mb-3">Advanced</h3>

    <div class="alert alert-secondary mt-n1">
      The Public API Key is optional and intentionally unused by the current server-side MVP. Leave it blank unless you
      are preparing a later storefront or browser-side integration.
    </div>

    <div class="mt-3">
      <%= preference_field(
        @integration,
        form,
        "plunk_public_api_key",
        i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
      ) %>
    </div>
    <p class="mb-0 mt-n2">
      Storing a Public API Key here does not enable client-side tracking on its own.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h3 class="h6 mb-3">Inbound unsubscribe webhook</h3>

    <div class="alert alert-warning mt-n1">
      Default off. Enable this only if you want Plunk <code>contact.unsubscribed</code> workflow events to write back into
      Spree and clear local newsletter consent by email.
    </div>

    <%= preference_field(
      @integration,
      form,
      "unsubscribe_webhook_enabled",
      i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
    ) %>
    <p class="mb-4 mt-n2">
      When enabled, configure a dedicated Plunk workflow webhook for <code>contact.unsubscribed</code> and send it to
      <code><%= plunk_unsubscribe_webhook_path(@integration) %></code>.
    </p>

    <%= preference_field(
      @integration,
      form,
      "unsubscribe_webhook_authorization_token",
      i18n_scope: "admin.integrations.plunk",
    ) %>
    <p class="mb-0 mt-n2">
      Required when the webhook is enabled. Send the same value as an <code>Authorization</code> header in Plunk using
      the format <code>Bearer your-secret-token</code>. The intake only accepts unsubscribe semantics and is designed to
      no-op safely when the email cannot be matched locally.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
